peVE.Stichera01.mode = misc_en_US_dedes.Mode5
peVE.Stichera01.melody = he.a.m5_en_US_dedes.ChairoisAskitikon.incipit
peVE.Stichera01.text = "Savior, nailed to the Cross, you erased * the curse incurred at the tree through another tree. * You died and were truly buried, and by your power as God * resurrected those who from all time had died. * We sing out and glorify Your dominion with sacred hymns. * You are the brightness of the Father, our very life, * O almighty Jesus, our Pascha and Passover. * Therefore the heavens now exult together with us on earth, * singing the hymns of Your triumph, triumphant Logos and Word of God, * O Christ, and the Ruler * over all, who is bestowing great mercy on the world."

peVE.Stichera02.mode = misc_en_US_dedes.Mode5
peVE.Stichera02.melody = he.a.m5_en_US_dedes.ChairoisAskitikon.incipit
peVE.Stichera02.text = "\"Say now, has Life gone down to the dead? * Is He, the never-setting Sun, still beneath the earth, * below in the nether regions?\" So did the Myrrh-bearers speak, * as they mourned and cried out, \"Come and let us go * with haste to His holy tomb, so that we might observe again.\" * And on arriving, they beheld in the sepulcher * a resplendent Angel, and they were very amazed. * He changed their mourning and lament to joy when he said to them, * \"O pious women, the Giver of Life has risen! Be not afraid. * And He reigns forever, as the Lord who is bestowing great mercy on the world.\""

peVE.Stichera03.mode = misc_en_US_dedes.Mode5
peVE.Stichera03.melody = he.a.m5_en_US_dedes.ChairoisAskitikon.incipit
peVE.Stichera03.text = "Early on Sunday morning, the host * of pious women sought the Sun, who before the sun * existed, and who had now set within the tomb. And they heard * the resplendent Angel say, \"Arisen is * the Light that went down and shined on the dead who in darkness slept. * To the Disciples go announce and proclaim to them. * Put away your grief and replace it with utter joy. * Joyfully celebrate in hearts unwavering that indeed * the world is granted salvation, this joyous Pascha and Passover. * For Christ has arisen, as the Lord who is bestowing great mercy on the world.\""

